        }
      ],
      "committedDate": "2026-05-26T18:36:58Z",
      "messageBody": "Preserve user signal delivery attributes and non-text content during Harness v1 history replay, normalize sandbox stream chunks into shell output events, and improve MastraCode runtime memory and startup recovery behavior.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Mastra Code (openai/gpt-5.5) <noreply@mastra.ai>",
      "messageHeadline": "fix(mastracode): tighten harness v1 compatibility",
      "oid": "ace45ed84ab8d3e4b43fa9bd8031468b52b01ef5"
    },
    {
      "authoredDate": "2026-05-26T22:42:50Z",
      "authors": [
        {
          "email": "tylerdbarnes@gmail.com",
          "id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0MTkwNzQz",
          "login": "TylerBarnes",
          "name": "Tyler Barnes"
        },
        {
          "email": "noreply@mastra.ai",
          "id": "",
          "login": "",
          "name": "Mastra Code (openai/gpt-5.5)"
        },
        {
          "email": "mbenhamd@gmail.com",
          "id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NzIwNDY3",
          "login": "mbenhamd",
          "name": "Mohamed BEN HAMDOUNE"
        }
      ],
      "committedDate": "2026-05-26T22:42:50Z",
      "messageBody": "This fixes a few Harness v1 issues that showed up while trying\nMastraCode locally. It's still not enough for it to work properly, but\nit gets it past a few issues.\n\nThe shared workspace factory now gets MastraCode runtime state, so\nstartup no longer fails when workspace setup needs `projectPath`:\n\n```ts\nworkspace: ({ requestContext }) =>\n  config.workspace!({\n    requestContext: this.withRuntimeHarnessContext(requestContext),\n    mastra: this.mastra,\n  })\n```\n\nThe internal v1 Mastra instance also matches legacy Harness logging\nbehavior, so expected storage capability noise does not leak into the\nTUI.\n\nYolo mode and MastraCode task tools now bypass v1 approval prompts\ncorrectly. `task_write`, `task_update`, `task_complete`, and\n`task_check` stay allowed even if permission rules are stricter.\n\n`request_access` now uses the native v1 sandbox-access resume path, and\nresume rebuilds the request context with model, memory, toolsets, yolo\nstate, and workspace context so approving sandbox access continues the\noriginal run instead of leaving it idle.\n\nValidated with focused mastracode/core tests and typechecks.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Mastra Code (openai/gpt-5.5) <noreply@mastra.ai>\nCo-authored-by: Mohamed BEN HAMDOUNE <mbenhamd@gmail.com>",
      "messageHeadline": "fix: stabilize MastraCode Harness v1 startup and resumes (#17042)",
      "oid": "e4c999d03b7745b72e2496e2683d3e28d9514ba0"
    },
    {
      "authoredDate": "2026-05-27T07:52:22Z",
      "authors": [
        {
          "email": "mbenhamd@gmail.com",
          "id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NzIwNDY3",
          "login": "mbenhamd",
          "name": "Mohamed BEN HAMDOUNE"
        }
      ],
      "committedDate": "2026-05-27T07:52:22Z",
      "messageBody": "…ness-v1-runtime\n\nResolve MastraCode Harness v1 runtime conflicts by preserving the runtime adapter path, carrying forward configDir propagation, and aligning sandbox access suspension with Harness v1 request ids.",
      "messageHeadline": "Merge branch 'feat/harness-v1-complete-core' into feat/mastracode-har…",
      "oid": "0f78a89815795b992bb7785370c7f5bfcebbdfd9"
    }
